## Change 7: GritQL Lint Rules to Enforce New Patterns

**Problem:** Without enforcement, new code can bypass the helpers and reintroduce raw SQL patterns. The project already has GritQL plugins for other patterns (no stdout.write in commands, no process.stdout).

**Solution:** Add 3 GritQL lint rules to `lint-rules/` and register them in `biome.jsonc`:

### Rule 1: `lint-rules/no-raw-metadata-queries.grit`

Bans raw `SELECT value FROM metadata` and `DELETE FROM metadata` queries, and direct `runUpsert` on the metadata table. Exempts `utils.ts` (defines the helpers) and `migration.ts` (schema bootstrapping).

```grit
file($name, $body) where {
  $name <: not r".*utils\.ts$",
  $name <: not r".*migration\.ts$",
  $body <: contains or {
    `$db.query($sql)` as $match where {
      $sql <: or { r".*SELECT value FROM metadata.*", r".*DELETE FROM metadata.*" }
    },
    `runUpsert($db, "metadata", $data, $keys)` as $match
  },
  register_diagnostic(span=$match, message="Use getMetadata/setMetadata/clearMetadata from db/utils.js instead of raw metadata queries.")
}
```

### Rule 2: `lint-rules/no-manual-transactions.grit`

Bans `db.exec("BEGIN TRANSACTION")`, `db.exec("COMMIT")`, `db.exec("ROLLBACK")`. Exempts `migration.ts`.

```grit
file($name, $body) where {
  $name <: not r".*migration\.ts$",
  $body <: contains `$db.exec($sql)` as $match where {
    $sql <: or { r".*BEGIN.*", r".*COMMIT.*", r".*ROLLBACK.*" }
  },
  register_diagnostic(span=$match, message="Use db.transaction()() instead of manual BEGIN/COMMIT/ROLLBACK.")
}
```

### Rule 3: `lint-rules/no-inline-touch-cache.grit`

Bans inline `UPDATE ... SET last_accessed` queries. Exempts `utils.ts` (defines the shared helper).

```grit
file($name, $body) where {
  $name <: not r".*utils\.ts$",
  $body <: contains `$db.query($sql).run($args)` as $match where {
    $sql <: r".*UPDATE .* SET last_accessed.*"
  },
  register_diagnostic(span=$match, message="Use touchCacheEntry() from db/utils.js instead of inline last_accessed UPDATE.")
}
```

**Biome config update (`biome.jsonc`):**
```jsonc
"plugins": [
  "./lint-rules/no-stdout-write-in-commands.grit",
  "./lint-rules/no-process-stdout-in-commands.grit",
  "./lint-rules/no-raw-metadata-queries.grit",      // NEW
  "./lint-rules/no-manual-transactions.grit",        // NEW
  "./lint-rules/no-inline-touch-cache.grit"          // NEW
]
```

**Files created:**
- `lint-rules/no-raw-metadata-queries.grit`
- `lint-rules/no-manual-transactions.grit`
- `lint-rules/no-inline-touch-cache.grit`

**Files modified:**
- `biome.jsonc` — Add 3 plugins

**Note:** The `project-aliases.ts` global touch (`UPDATE project_aliases SET last_accessed = ?` without WHERE) is intentionally different from the per-key helper. After Change 2/3 are applied, the remaining global touch (line 19) should get a `// biome-ignore` suppression comment.

**Tests to verify:**
```bash
bun run lint                          # All 3 new rules fire on pre-refactor code
# After refactoring, rules should pass clean
```

